	<h2>Types of Hearing Protection We Offer</h2>

	<h3>Ready-Made Hearing Protection</h3>
	<p>
		Ready-made hearing protection options are a convenient and budget-friendly
		way to reduce noise exposure in everyday situations. They are widely
		available, easy to use, and provide reliable protection for short-term or
		occasional use when you need quick hearing safety on the go.
	</p>
	<Accordion>
		<AccordionItem title="Earplugs">
			<p>
				Earplugs are small devices that are inserted into the ear canal to
				help reduce overall noise levels. They are commonly used at concerts,
				sporting events, loud restaurants, or other noisy environments where
				sound exposure can quickly become uncomfortable. Disposable foam
				options and reusable styles are both available, offering varying
				levels of comfort and noise reduction depending on your needs.
			</p>
		</AccordionItem>
		<AccordionItem title="Semi-Insert Earplugs">
			<p>
				Semi-insert earplugs feature soft tips connected by a flexible band
				that rests either under the chin or behind the head. This design makes
				them easy to remove and reinsert throughout the day, making them a
				great option for people who move in and out of noisy environments.
				They are often used in workplace settings or for intermittent noise
				exposure where convenience is key.
			</p>
		</AccordionItem>
		<AccordionItem title="Earmuffs">
			<p>
				Earmuffs provide high-level protection by fully covering the outer ear
				and creating a seal that blocks sound. They are commonly used in
				louder environments such as shooting ranges, construction sites,
				landscaping, or yardwork. Because they are worn over the ear, they are
				easy to put on and take off and can be worn over earplugs for
				additional protection when needed.
			</p>
		</AccordionItem>
	</Accordion>
	<p class="note-italic">
		While ready-made options are effective and accessible, they typically don't
		provide the same level of secure fit, comfort, or long-term wearability as
		custom-molded hearing protection, especially for individuals who need
		consistent or all-day use.
	</p>

	<h3>Custom Hearing Protection</h3>
	<p>
		For the highest level of comfort, performance, and long-term use, custom
		protection is often the best choice. These devices are individually molded
		to the unique shape of your ear, creating a secure, comfortable fit and
		more consistent noise reduction compared to standard options. Because they
		are custom-made, they are ideal for frequent or extended use and can be
		tailored to different listening environments.
	</p>
	<p>Custom Options Include:</p>
	<Accordion>
		<AccordionItem title="Custom Earplugs">
			<p>
				Custom earplugs are designed for individuals who are regularly exposed
				to loud environments, such as musicians, industrial workers, or anyone
				who needs dependable noise reduction throughout the day. They provide a
				comfortable, secure fit that stays in place longer and offers more
				consistent protection than disposable options.
			</p>
		</AccordionItem>
		<AccordionItem title="Impulse Filter Earplugs">
			<p>
				These specialized earplugs are ideal for hunters and shooters. They
				are designed to reduce sudden, high-intensity sounds, like gunfire,
				while still allowing softer sounds such as speech, movement, and
				environmental cues to be heard clearly. This balance helps protect
				hearing without sacrificing awareness.
			</p>
		</AccordionItem>
		<AccordionItem title="Sleep Plugs">
			<p>
				Custom sleep plugs are made from soft, flexible materials designed for
				comfort during extended wear. They gently reduce background noise at
				night, helping improve sleep quality without creating pressure or
				discomfort, even when lying on your side.
			</p>
		</AccordionItem>
		<AccordionItem title="Musician In-Ear Monitors (IEMs)">
			<p>
				In-ear monitors are designed for performers and musicians who need
				clear, high-quality sound on stage or in rehearsal. They deliver a
				balanced audio mix directly to the ears while helping maintain safe
				listening levels, protecting hearing without compromising performance
				quality.
			</p>
		</AccordionItem>
		<AccordionItem title="Digital Hearing Protection (SoundGear)">
			<p>
				Advanced digital protection systems are designed for high-noise
				environments such as hunting, shooting, or industrial settings. These
				devices actively amplify safe, low-level sounds while instantly
				reducing harmful loud noise, offering both protection and situational
				awareness in one solution.
			</p>
		</AccordionItem>
	</Accordion>

