	<h2>Materials for Custom Ear Molds</h2>
	<p>
		Custom ear molds are available in a variety of materials, allowing us to
		match comfort, durability, and performance to your individual needs and
		lifestyle. Each material offers unique benefits depending on how and where
		your hearing devices or protection will be used.
	</p>
	<ul>
		<li>
			<strong>Acrylic:</strong> A hard, durable material with a smooth finish.
			It's easy to clean, long-lasting, and offers a very stable fit.
		</li>
		<li>
			<strong>Vinyl:</strong> A softer, more flexible option that's often
			preferred for sensitive ears. It provides added comfort for all-day wear.
		</li>
		<li>
			<strong>Silicone:</strong> The softest and most flexible option. It's very
			comfortable, water-resistant, and ideal for active use or all-day wear.
		</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>How Custom Ear Molds Are Made</h2>
	<p>The process is simple and comfortable:</p>
	<ol>
		<li>
			An audiologist takes an impression of your ear using soft medical-grade
			silicone material.
		</li>
		<li>The impression is sent to a specialized lab.</li>
		<li>
			Your custom ear protection is created in the material and style you
			prefer.
		</li>
	</ol>
	<p>
		The result is a secure, comfortable fit you can depend on for hours at a
		time.
	</p>

	<h2>How Long Do Custom Earplugs Last?</h2>
	<p>
		With routine care, custom earplugs typically last 3 to 5 years. Lifespan
		may vary depending on use, cleaning habits, and natural changes in your
		ears over time. We recommend periodic checkups to ensure they continue to
		fit comfortably and provide optimal protection.
	</p>

	<h2>Frequently Asked Questions About Hearing Protection</h2>
	<Accordion>
		<AccordionItem title="How do I clean custom earplugs or molds?">
			<p>
				Custom earplugs or molds should be cleaned regularly to maintain
				comfort and performance. Wipe them daily with a soft, dry cloth to
				remove wax or debris. For a deeper clean, you can use mild soap and
				warm water, then allow them to air dry completely before reuse. Avoid
				alcohol wipes or harsh cleaning agents, as they can dry out or damage
				the material over time.
			</p>
		</AccordionItem>
		<AccordionItem title="Can I wear custom plugs with helmets or safety gear?">
			<p>
				Yes. Custom earplugs are designed to sit comfortably within the ear
				canal, making them compatible with helmets, hard hats, masks, and
				other protective equipment. Because they don't sit outside the ear like
				traditional earmuffs, they provide a secure, low-profile fit that won't
				interfere with other safety gear.
			</p>
		</AccordionItem>
		<AccordionItem title="Do earplugs block all sound?">
			<p>
				No. Earplugs do not block all sound. Instead, they are designed to
				reduce overall noise levels to safer, more comfortable ranges while
				still allowing important sounds, such as speech, alarms, or
				environmental cues, to be heard. This balance helps protect your
				hearing without completely isolating you from your surroundings.
			</p>
		</AccordionItem>
		<AccordionItem title="Are custom plugs worth it?">
			<p>
				Absolutely. Custom earplugs offer a personalized fit that provides
				superior comfort, better noise reduction, and long-term durability
				compared to disposable options. For individuals who are frequently
				exposed to loud environments, they are a worthwhile investment in both
				hearing protection and everyday comfort.
			</p>
		</AccordionItem>
	</Accordion>

